                        <p>In other news, 700 students in the Class of 2019 today published a joint letter in The New York Times also titled “Here’s why I refused to read ‘The Very Hungry Caterpillar’.” The letter says only the word “Laziness.”</p>
<p><em>Monday Monday would like to propose the script for the&nbsp;"Minions" movie as the Class of 2020’s summer reading. </em></p>

